{"_id":"25bf63c1e43c2fcd","name":"Coral of the Sea Fairy","type":"object","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/pearl-natural-red.webp","system":{"description":"A lump of blood-red coral containing the trapped soul of the Sea Fairy. This cursed item was created by killing the fairy and harnessing her essence. The coral pulses with ancient sea magic and grants its possessor limited access to the fairy's powers, including healing waters, summoning waves, and instant sea travel. However, sea creatures sense what has been done and will attack the bearer without hesitation to free the fairy's soul. (Special Scenario Gift for Marina the Sea Explorer)","quantity":1,"weight":2,"value":1000,"equipped":false,"properties":["Magical","Cursed","Grants sea powers","Attracts hostile sea creatures","Unique"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"592186c153ef9830","name":"Hans' Experimental Pistols","type":"object","img":"icons/weapons/guns/gun-pistol-flintlock.webp","system":{"description":"A pair of prized experimental pistols that Hans bought from an inventor for more than half of his war earnings. These guns can fire multiple shots at the same time, allowing the wielder to aim at 3 targets within a 30-foot square area with one attack. One pistol can be fired while the other is being reloaded as an additional action.","quantity":2,"weight":4,"value":500,"equipped":false,"properties":["Multi-shot","Quick reload","Experimental technology","High value"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"d535f555b571006c","name":"Hans' Smoke Bombs","type":"object","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-corked-fumes-purple.webp","system":{"description":"Experimental smoke bombs used by Hans to surprise enemies. When deployed, thick smoke covers a 30-foot square area. Everyone inside receives penalties for actions requiring sight, except for Hans who has learned to fight blind. The smoke also allows Hans to escape from engaged opponents without being prevented.","quantity":3,"weight":1,"value":50,"equipped":false,"properties":["Creates smoke cloud","30-foot area","Tactical escape tool","Single use"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"b0e174c69b056884","name":"Letter from Nils to the Riksråd","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-sealed-red-yellow.webp","system":{"description":"An urgent letter sent by Nils (called the Poor Devil) to the Riksråd, the great council of the Kingdom of Sweden, imploring them to help him and his former comrades. The letter describes how six valiant soldiers - all that remained of their company after the bloody war between Sweden and Russia - are being killed one by one by a monster that seems able to take a bullet without batting an eye. Two comrades have already fallen to the monster's fury when the letter was written.","location":"Given to Hunters by the Order","importance":"crucial","found":true,"scenario":"a-soldiers-duty"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"27c8878cdfbb2d27","name":"Nils' War Diary","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-worn-brown-tan.webp","system":{"description":"A worn diary belonging to Nils the Poor Devil, containing detailed accounts of what happened six years ago. The pages reveal Enar's identity, his relationship with Satu, and the brutal punishment inflicted upon him by his comrades - though the abuse perpetrated by Andersen was never discovered by his fellow soldiers. The writing makes it clear that the punishment reserved for Enar was beyond reason.","location":"Nils' house in Sundsvall","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"a-soldiers-duty"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"45893b4b8e1d8426","name":"Seashells from the Cliff","type":"clue","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/token-shell-yellow.webp","system":{"description":"Seashells that fell from Enar's transformed body during combat. Erik recognizes these as identical to shells he collected when he lived with his mother in a small cliffside village. According to old stories, under that cliff there is a dense network of caves where a Sea Fairy is said to reside - the same fairy who gave Enar his immortal form.","location":"Andersen's estate (after first encounter with Enar)","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"a-soldiers-duty"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
